<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <title>Palindrome Checker</title>
    </head>
    <body>
    <main>
        <article>
            <header>
                <h1>{{title}}</h1>
            </header>
                <p>
                A palindrome is a phrase that is spelled the same way, backwards and forwards. For example, the following phrases are palindromes: "Madam", "Was it a cat I saw?".
                </p>
                <form action="/result" method="post">
                    <label for="text-to-test">Input text for palindromity:</label>
                    <input type="text" name="text-to-test" id="text-to-test">
                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
                </form>
            </article>
        </main>
        </body>
    </html>
    